docs.snippet: Rockwell is poised to join a handful of artists whose work is recognizable not just for its artistic quality but for the millions it took to acquire one....
docs.lead_paragraph: Rockwell is poised to join a handful of artists whose work is recognizable not just for its artistic quality but for the millions it took to acquire one.
docs.abstract: James B Stewart Common Sense column; Norman Rockwell, once seen as lowly illustrator and calendar artist, is now undergoing major critical and financial reappraisal; major auction houses Sothby's and Christie's built their spring sales of American art around two of his paintings, which sold for $9.1 million and $22.1 million, respectively; Rockwell auction record is $46 million; surge in price of his art dates to at least 2001.

headline.main: Norman Rockwell’s Art, Once Sniffed At, Is Becoming Prized
headline.print_headline: Norman Rockwell’s Art, Once Sniffed At, Is Becoming Prized
